    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "I know it&#39;s late reply, you can take a look at <a href=\"https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-loaded\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Spring Loaded</a> - , which is a JVM agent for reloading class file changes whilst a JVM is running. It transforms classes at loadtime to make them amenable to later reloading. Unlike &#39;hot code replace&#39; which only allows simple changes once a JVM is running (e.g. changes to method bodies), Spring Loaded allows you to add/modify/delete methods/fields/constructors and more..."
